The paper focuses on the study of geometric and topological graphs, which falls under the category of computational geometry (cs.CG). The paper also deals with extremal problems and graph drawing problems, which are related to discrete mathematics (cs.DM) and graph theory (cs.GT). The study of nearly-planar graphs also involves the analysis of graph density, which is a topic in computational and discrete mathematics (cs.DS). Finally, the paper discusses the readability of graph drawings, which is a topic in human-computer interaction and information visualization (cs.SI).
